[x] E over interactable Objects

"Mallacht-

- Teaches keyboard fluency!!! This can also translate to improved letter recognition.
- Intertwines literacy through reading and comprehension, as well as being introduced to a new realm through game play.
- Is there a clear goal or is it just explorative learning? Many 6th graders, or 6th grade educators, may want an end goal or specific mission... This could also be done through a level sequence or specific learning goals 
- If it's done in an educational environment, there most likely has to be some type of learning goal or learning objective to make it relevant to the curriculum/instruction or something that is able to be planned into a lesson plan with purpose."
To me, this makes it sound like really the only improvement they would suggest is that it needs to be just a little more clear that you're learning about Fae / Celtic folklore. This can be very simple (And I would recommend making it very simple given there's only 4.5 days left!) I'm thinking something like some text before the game starts:

*Black background, white text"
"My mother was taken by the Fae.
I need to learn their tricks if I can rescue her."

Something like that will both avoid just throwing the player in without any context, and will make your educational goal much more clear to players who don't have your project description. Obviously you are free to do something else, as long as you meet the requirement of:
The player knows they are learning about Celtic folklore to rescue their mother

